#Text=Marple ( Pennsylvania )
#Text=Marple
#Text=is in Delaware County , Pennsylvania ( commonly referred to as Delco ) .
#Text=Marple is about 11 miles from center city Philadelphia with a population of more than 23,000 .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Marple was inhabited in 1683 by a group of Quakers who were members of the Society of Friends .
#Text=The Quakers escaped from England and the religious persecution present there and settled in the land of William Penn ’s Holy Experiment .
#Text=The Holy experiment was an attempt by the Quakers to establish their own community .

#Text=The community began to grow during the pre-revolutionary period , and while no action took place in Marple during the Revolutionary War , the growth of occupation crafts such as weavers and millers gave way to increased trade .
#Text=Once the war was over , Marple returned to its farming and agrarian lifestyle .
#Text=Population in Marple began to grow rapidly after the Civil War .
#Text=The Industrial Revolution brought rail transportation through the township making transportation easier around Marple and into Philadelphia .
#Text=The largest period of development for Marple Township came towards the end of World War II .
#Text=The improvement of roads , public transportation and the availability of the automobiles made Marple a suburban community .
#Text=Nowadays , Marple is a bustling community full of families , great restaurants , tons of shopping experiences nearby , and great attractions .
#Text=Whether you are more family oriented , a history buff , a foodie or a shopaholic , Marple is a great central town to everything you need .
#Text=Located 11 miles from Philadelphia and 13 miles from the King of Prussia Mall , everything you will need is within a 30 minute car drive .
#Text=Get in
#Text=By car , Marple is most easily accessible from Interstate 476 ( The Blue Route ) at exit 9-Broomall/Upper Darby at the junction of I-476 and Route 3 , known as West Chester Pike .
#Text=The Septa Public Transportation system hub at 69th Street in Upper Darby is a easy and accessible way to get around Delaware County and surrounding areas .
#Text=Route 104 on the Septa System will take riders from center city Philadelphia directly into Marple .
#Text=Also , taking the Market-Frankfurt line from Philadelphia into 69th Street Station will leave you only a short drive away from Marple .
#Text=Additionally , Marple is only 17 miles from Philadelphia International Airport , which makes traveling to and from Marple very accessible .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Getting around Marple is very easy .
#Text=Driving by car is probably the easiest and most common option .
#Text=There is an abundance of parking throughout Marple , which makes driving the best option .
#Text=Most developments are located close to stores or shopping centers and sidewalks are present throughout the township , making walking or biking easy as well .
#Text=See
#Text=Thomas Massey House
#Text=–
#Text=This home is an American Classic and is on the National Register of Historical Places .
#Text=It is an old farmhouse from 1686 .
#Text=Once the home of an indentured servant who became a landowner , it is one of the oldest English Quaker homes in all of Pennsylvania .
#Text=Delaware County Historical Society
#Text=– founded in 1895 , it is the oldest historical society in the county .

#Text=The mission of the Delaware County historical society is to preserve and present the history of Delaware County and surrounding areas , including restoration of historic structures , historical objects and archival materials .
#Text=Greek American Society of Greater Philadelphia
#Text=This great museum is host to a wide range of Greek American history , reflected the strong Greek community in Marple .
#Text=Do
#Text=The eleven parks located in Marple Township are all kept and maintained by the municipal government .
#Text=Broomall Fields
#Text=fields for Marple Township Little League .
#Text=Marple Gardens
#Text=offers softball fields and basketball courts , playground and picnic areas .
#Text=Old Marple School Park
#Text=playground , picnic area , sledding hill and walking trails .
#Text=South Marple Little League
#Text=baseball fields , roller rink , tennis courts and snack bar .
#Text=Veterans Park
#Text=large playground and walking trails around a large open field along with entertainment gazebo great for photo opportunities .
#Text=Buy
#Text=Lawrence Park Shopping Center

#Text=located on Sproul and Lawrence Roads , LPSC is home to many stores including Barnes & Noble , TJ Maxx , Radio Shack , Home Goods , Hallmark , local florist , Citizens Bank , Acme Supermarkets , Panera Bread , Hair Cuttery , Nana 's Attic Thrift Store and more .
#Text=Eat
#Text=It is important to note that Marple is a dry township , but many restaurants are BYOB .
#Text=Soprano ’s Deli and Catering
#Text=3072 West Chester Pike , Broomall PA , BYOB , best canoli 's in town .
#Text=Country Squire Diner
#Text=2560 West Chester Pike , Broomall PA .
#Text=Offers great food 24 hours with a delicious bakery .
#Text=Valentino 's Ristorante Italiano
#Text=2902
#Text=West Chester Pike , Broomall PA , BYOB with a great selection of Italian cuisine .
#Text=Mrs Marty 's Deli
#Text=1991 Sproul Road , Broomall PA , located in Pawrence Park Shopping Center , family run deli/restaurant with great food all day long .
#Text=Garden China
#Text=2047 Sproul Road , Broomall PA , quick and delicious Chinese restaurant .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=There are no hotels/motels in Marple but there are many located in Springfield , Conshohocken , and outside of Philadelphia .
#Text=Go next
#Text=Marple is located in a great central area between Philadelphia and the rural areas of the western suburbs .
#Text=It is easily accessible to the farm country of the western suburbs and the city life and attractions of the big city .
#Text=Media
#Text=– located about 15 minutes from Marple offers a great dining and shopping experience in a quaint and adorable town .
#Text=Brandywine Battle Historic Field
#Text=– brings to life the largest engagement of the Revolutionary War .
#Text=Linvilla Orchards
#Text=– a 300 acre farm dedicated to agriculture , family fun and education .
#Text=Pick your own fruits and vegetables or visit around holidays for special events .
#Text=Longwood Gardens
#Text=– a beautiful garden experience inspiring visitors through design , horticulture and education of the arts .
#Text=Tyler Arboretum
#Text=– offers year round hiking trails , horticulture collections and rare plant specimens , great for families and outdoor enthusiasts .
